  *
  * This class bridges the layering between Engine and D3DDrv.
  *
+ * On PC, FMovieTexture is a real FTexture: the engine cache locks the
+ * D3D surface and calls GetTextureData to fill it from a CPU BGRA buffer
+ * the D3DDrv-side decoder produces. SetMovieMaterial pumps the decoder
+ * via the UCMovieMaterialPump export, bumping a revision counter; the
+ * cache picks up the revision change and re-uploads through the standard
+ * UTexture pipeline. No Direct3DTexture8 swap, no AddRef/Release on
+ * cache pointers, no cache-hash mutation.
+ *
+ * The PC-side decoder lives in D3DDrv (D3DMoviePlayback.cpp). We reach
+ * it via GetProcAddress against D3DDrv.dll, mirroring how D3DDrv talks
+ * to ALAudio for cutscene-audio ducking.
+ *
  * ============================================================================
  */
